1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,400
OK, I'm going to tell you a little bit about how

2
00:00:02,400 --> 00:00:05,640
a very small team, it was three people for most

3
00:00:05,640 --> 00:00:09,280
of the development, built Cloud Design in about 10 weeks

4
00:00:09,280 --> 00:00:10,880
from idea to launching the product.

5
00:00:10,880 --> 00:00:13,120
And the reason I'm going to share these things with you

6
00:00:13,120 --> 00:00:15,300
is because the most common question I get asked

7
00:00:15,300 --> 00:00:17,520
is, why did you decide to start working on this?

8
00:00:17,520 --> 00:00:20,240
How did you see that this was an opportunity for building

9
00:00:20,240 --> 00:00:22,360
a new AI-enabled product?

10
00:00:22,360 --> 00:00:23,240
How'd you build it?

11
00:00:23,240 --> 00:00:25,180
How'd you launch it?

12
00:00:25,180 --> 00:00:26,719
So everything I'm going to cover here,

13
00:00:26,719 --> 00:00:28,680
there is no real secret sauce.

14
00:00:28,680 --> 00:00:30,920
These are all things that work well for us.

15
00:00:30,920 --> 00:00:31,719
Take what you like.

16
00:00:31,719 --> 00:00:35,360
You can do a lot of these things tomorrow.

17
00:00:35,360 --> 00:00:38,520
To start, I want to tell you about what Anthropic Labs is.

18
00:00:38,520 --> 00:00:39,320
It's kind of funny.

19
00:00:39,320 --> 00:00:42,360
It's a lab inside a frontier lab.

20
00:00:42,360 --> 00:00:44,240
We don't have any labs within Anthropic Labs,

21
00:00:44,240 --> 00:00:47,040
but it is labs quite a ways down.

22
00:00:47,040 --> 00:00:51,439
The way that we usually talk about it is as a bet factory.

23
00:00:51,439 --> 00:00:54,299
And by that, I mean we have very small teams exploring

24
00:00:54,299 --> 00:00:56,720
the frontier of what the models can do

25
00:00:56,720 --> 00:01:00,279
and making bets about whether or not something will work.

26
00:01:00,279 --> 00:01:03,599
We run experiments to find out what works.

27
00:01:03,599 --> 00:01:05,879
We double down on the things that are working.

28
00:01:05,879 --> 00:01:08,839
We fold the things that are not working.

29
00:01:08,839 --> 00:01:12,440
And at any given time, we might have a dozen small teams

30
00:01:12,440 --> 00:01:15,400
exploring different concepts.

31
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:18,400
So it's lots of exploration, small number

32
00:01:18,400 --> 00:01:20,480
of really high conviction releases of things

33
00:01:20,480 --> 00:01:23,080
that we think can be moonshots or change how

34
00:01:23,080 --> 00:01:26,120
people work with the models.

35
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:28,919
There's a few products that came from here that you may know.

36
00:01:28,919 --> 00:01:31,320
Cloud Code came out of labs.


